    'loading.tsx = automatically shown while page data loads. error.tsx = shown when an error occurs.',
    'Dynamic routes use square brackets: [id] in the folder name becomes a variable in the URL.',
    'Route groups use parentheses: (dashboard) groups routes without adding to the URL path.',
    'Nested layouts: each folder can have its own layout.tsx that wraps only that folder\'s routes.',
], TEAL_MID)
story.append(sp(6))

story.append(label('HOW TO SAY IT IN AN INTERVIEW'))
story.append(interview_box(
    'How does routing work in Next.js App Router? How is it different from React Router?',
